reviews.review_text: 24 bit in all its glory sounds awesome

Take a step back! Was personally at this show and is pretty solid from start to finish..but the one song that I still go back to from this one is the EYES OF THE WORLD...BAM SHACKA LACKA!! The sound quality is top notch..Give it a whirl

Stellar 2nd set - Great sound One of the best 2nd sets of summer 1990 (not better than the next show in Buffalo, but solid and full of energy).  It was a very hot afternoon in Massachusetts and the opener set from Edie and the Bohemians is worth seeking out.  

The first set was a little slow and lacked energy; but, given the heat of the day, it was appreciated as the main floor was packed to the limits and it was just too hot.  Good set, just nothing like the 2nd set.  I can still remember those large video screens with a big smiling Jerry and Brent.  

This was the 3rd show of 4 for me that summer (started in Raleigh) and the only one that I didn't have a ticket for when I arrived at the show.  Got this beautiful mail order in the lot (thank you again!): http://www.flickr.com/photos/mrsoulmark/9287488392/
Love the crystal clear sound on this one.  This is the version to stream.
